headline: Costco Lawsuit Over Rotisserie Chicken Contamination And Investor Considerations
summary: Costco Wholesale is facing a proposed class action lawsuit alleging its rotisserie chicken products may carry a salmonella contamination risk. The complaint centers on production at a Nebraska processing plant and claims Costco did not adequately control or disclose potential food safety risks. The case focuses on Costco's handling of rotisserie chicken, a high profile item in its warehouse clubs that plays a key role in customer traffic and loyalty.
